European inflation slides into food
The accelerated inflation in the euro area is primarily due to the vertiginous rise in food prices.
The increase in prices in November was higher than expected in the 13 countries of the euro area, recording - after 2.6 percent in October - an annual inflation of 3.1 percent, the Union Statistics Office based in Luxembourg announced.
Official forecasts were only 3 percent likely, Bloomberg.
The European Central Bank (ECB), unlike the U.S., British and Canadian issuing banks, did not cut the basic interest rate, under the pretext that the decline, along with rising commodity prices and the reduction of forced unemployment, would provoke an inflation spiral.
The ECB wants to keep the inflation rate below, but at least close to two percent.
According to one analyst, the ECB is in the 22nd trap: "it is necessary to negotiate" on inflation so that later it does not have to intervene on this issue.
Inflation of 3.3 percent, recorded in Germany, beat the twelve-year record; while in Spain it increased from 3.6 percent to 4.1 percent.
Inflation has risen in the eurozone as a result of high food and energy prices.
Wheat quotations increased by 88 percent and soybean quotations reached their highest level since 1973.
Similarly, much more was paid in 2007 for vegetable oil and dairy products.
The price of crude oil in the world market rose this year by 52 percent, reaching already last month the black gold almost $100 a barrel.
According to the ECB, inflation in 2008 will jump from 2.1 percent today to 2.5 percent, while for 2009 it will decrease to 1.9.
According to analysts, annual inflation will remain around 3 percent in the next three to four months, but the average annual rate will be 2.1 percent.
At the same time, during the year 2008 the ECB is expected to reduce interest rates twice.
Gallup predicts a government crisis
After a long stagnation, for early December the support of the Young Democrats Alliance increased significantly, reaching its highest level since 2002, while the Gallup never before experienced such a low level — 13 percent — in the case of the Socialists.
The difference in the case of the secure voters of the parties – due to the greater firmness of the opposition voters – would mean a support of more than two-thirds (an 71 percent) versus a support of a fifth for the socialists (an 20 percent).
According to the poll, the Democratic Forum and the Alliance of Free Democrats would not even reach the necessary limit to have any parliamentary seat: their support within the total population is two percent.
Among the safe voters there are one percent more supporters on both sides.
The economic environment continued to deteriorate even compared to the previous low point – it has never been so high, 41 percent of those who judged the country’s economic situation bad, while another 46 percent believes the situation is quite bad.
Families, after the most hopeful expectations of spring and summer, are now more pessimistic about changing their own economic situation.
As for the coming year, the majority of the population has a deteriorating situation and only one-tenth expect an improvement.
In December, 71 percent of respondents, higher than any previous Gallup poll, estimated that the Prime Minister was performing his duties rather badly than well.
13% of respondents trust or trust Ferenc Gyurcsány a lot, while Viktor Orbán has the support of 38% of respondents.
54 percent of the population do not trust the head of government at all and 27 percent do not trust the president of the Alliance of Young Democrats.
One of the indicators of the configuration of the political situation is that, what proportion of society thinks it is possible to control the discontent experienced in front of the person of the Head of Government without a change of government.
While after the October riots last year 35 percent estimated that it would be desirable to keep the government and the head of government in power, currently this proportion is only 20 percent, while the relative majority (33 percent) believes that the only solution is to hold new elections.
Interest in the referendum is characterized by the fact that 60 percent of respondents to the question about participation answered that they would participate and another 20 percent said it is likely to participate.
In a comparative way, only 55 percent of the population would participate in "a general election to be held this Sunday" and another 15 percent believes its participation is likely.
74 per cent of the population would disapprove of the payment of study fees, 79 per cent of the medical consultation service and 84 per cent of hospital care.
If we observe these proportions only among the safe participants in the referendum, 81, 84 and 89 percent of voters would reject the introduction of study fees, payment for medical consultations and hospital care.
The most expensive is Auchan, Tesco has fifty-folded its prices
The Budaörs gold trade triangle hypermarketsined the average price level rise of 16 percent, with the difference that this year VAT has not been raised.
Posts by Napi Gazdaság
This year also increased by an average of 16 percent in the Budaörs gold commercial triangle the daily Napi’s usual Christmas basket, but in all hypermarkets a growth was recorded far above 1,000 HUF.
As in December of last year prices in food supermarkets had already "shown" so there was no drastic percentage increase compared to the high starting point.
However, it is obviously frightening for consumers that what they were able to buy last year at a price well below 9,000 HUF, today they can’t do it even for 10,000.
Napi’s basket in the hypermarkets studied exceeded the psychological limit of ten thousand HUF with a minimum of 91 HUF.
And the highest-value basket was 10 573 HUF.
(In the year 2003 that basket cost 6800 HUF.)
The price of Unicum liquor and fish remained almost at the level of the previous year, but there was a sharp increase in the filet of duckfish, the nut and the seed of amapola.
The price of wheat flour and bread followed the data of the Central Bureau of Statistics, although in the Auchan we have also found one kilogram of bread for the price of 139 HUF.
Competition did not lower the price of the product to less than 200 HUF.
It was also surprising in this store that the price of the Coca-Cola with a two-litre redemptive bottle cost less than 200 HUF, so that this product, even with the price of the bottle, cost only 257 HUF.
However, in Napi’s basket, Auchan was the most expensive, while Cora was the cheapest.
According to our calculations, with respect to last year’s Christmas prices, Cora increased by 15 percent, while Tesco and Auchan with about 18 percent the prices listed in Napi’s basket.
Comparing the values of the most expensive basket last year with that of the cheapest basket this year, the difference has been 12 percent, while the growth between the cheapest last year and the most expensive this year has been 21 percent.
The average growth was 1480 HUF.
Last year the average price growth was 1206 HUF, so during Christmas last year in prices the increase in VAT was felt.
Just this process destroyed trade, the supermarkets were visibly unable to decide on the price margin to be applied to each product and to calculate the effect of price change on consumption.
(If the trader misplans the speed of a product’s circulation, he may lose a significant profit on the margin that matches the sales volume.)
The increase in the price of Napi’s basket reached such extremes as a result of the increase in VAT, which was higher by 1720 HUF than the value registered in 2006, while in the cheapest the difference was only 844 HUF.
Such extremes did not occur this year, as the highest price so far has been 1630 HUF more than last year and the cheapest also increased by 1284 HUF.
Comparing the two Christmas seasons, a catastrophic price growth was recorded in less than 20 months, in the hypermarkets the price of consumer goods grew more than 30 percent.
(H, this does not necessarily confirm the figures of the Central Bureau of Statistics: this office, in the case of some foods of the first necessity recorded in the 12-month interval a price increase of more than 30 percent.
For example, in addition to wheat, also in the case of eggs.)
According to Napi’s basket, in this latter case this seems almost impossible, because in the price of this product that was quite expensive already last year compared to the base, it was recorded, in the worst of cases, only a 10 percent increase in prices.
According to all indices, flour suppliers have a stronger position than egg suppliers, which can impose drastic price increases even on multinationals.
Hypermarkets do not complain about the gold commercial triangle, they constantly talk about positive results.
According to our collected experiences, most consumers in the three stores visited are no longer interested in prices.
Of all the products they buy large amounts, carrying the preserved foods by pallets.
On Wednesday morning, large queues were formed in the three stores in front of the boxes because the number of customers suddenly increased.
However, we have information that within the country the sales volumes are lower, numerous multinationals complain to the survey institutes because the revenues are below their plans and not only in the case of food, but also in the case of household appliances.
Many hospitals use disinfectants.
This year, several thousand infections have been registered in hospitals, primarily due to the misuse of antibiotics.
The prevailing hygiene conditions in hospitals, the clogging of the beds and the overload of staff do not favor the control of infections, says the head of department of the National Center for Epidemiology.
In many hospitals it is saved even with disinfectants.
Not long ago a MRSA infection was diagnosed in the traumatology department of János Hospital.
In a man hospitalized after a serious accident, the presence of antibiotic-resistant bacteria was detected.
The patient was isolated.
The same type of infection occurred in this same hospital at the beginning of the year.
One injured in a serious car accident was discharged from the hospital and the same patient soon after had to return to the hospital as a result of the contagion with MRSA and since then it has not been possible to perform an important surgical intervention due to the presence of the bacterium in his body.
As of December 10, this year, 1094 cases of hospital infection produced by multi-resistant agents have been recorded in the National Nosocomialis Surveillance System - said Karolina Böröcz, chief medical officer of the National Center for Epidemiology.
This means that in hospitals this number of infections produced by multi-resistant agents has been recorded with certainty, of the rest there is no information.
Nearly two-thirds of infections (683 cases) are due to MRSA, i.e. Staphylococcus aureus, resistant to methicillin-oxacillin.
A third of humans carry Staphylococcus aureus (SA) bacteria in their nose without causing any disease.
SA-produced infections (e.g. throat inflammation, tonsillitis, skin infections, wound infections) react well to antibiotics and are easy to treat.
However, once it is applied overly or unnecessarily to antibiotics, bacteria that normally react well to antibiotics are transformed into bacteria very resistant to antibiotics and quickly contain in inadequate hospital conditions.
They can cause serious hospital infections, such as wound infections or septicemia, primarily in patients with transient or chronic immunodeficiency, in patients with weakened bodies, in elderly people or in people with low weight.
In the opinion of the doctor-director of the János Hospital there is nothing special about MRSA infection, these infections are daily in hospitals.
Infection should not be confused with epidemic, MRSA is only absent – Tibor Nyulasi said – where its presence is not examined.
Resistant to antibiotics
“These patients are isolated, nursing staff treat them in rubber gloves and masks and there are the right antibiotics for their treatment,” said Tibor Nyulasi.
Hospitalized patients are examined in advance to verify the presence of MRSA in their bodies, but infection can not even be avoided in all cases.
It’s not fashionable to take samples.
It would be possible to prevent MRSA hospital infections in most cases, however the current national hospital circumstances do not favor for the prevention of formation and contagion with multi-resistant pathogens - says Karolina Böröcz.
Since this infection mainly occurs in hospitals and old-age homes, hospitals should examine hospitalized patients and immediately isolate patients who carry MRSA in their bodies.
However, microbiological sampling is not fashionable in Hungarian hospitals.
This is also due to the fact that the National Health Fund does not fund these medical examinations.
So most cases come to the public light when visible MRSA infections are already occurring in the patient - said the chief medical department of the epidemiological center.
The European Union makes strict orders for the application of antibiotics in human medicine and there are also national directives for treating infections and pathological frames.
Antibiotic therapy should be targeted, i.e. microbiological tests should be carried out to prevent resistance to drugs, but hospitals do not always meet this requirement.
Microbiological sampling is even less common in the case of ambulant patients or in basic care - said Karolina Böröcz.
Avoid using disinfectants
Scientific experiments have shown that in most cases MRSA is transmitted from one patient to another through healthcare personnel.
Therefore, handwashing, the use of rubber gloves and masks play a very important role, but also in this sense considerable flaws are experienced in hospitals.
MRSA is transmitted by droplets and by direct contact between people, but in national hospital circumstances it is not always possible to isolate the infected patient.
Moreover, the hospital rooms are often crowded, the beds are often very close together, although to prevent the epidemic, patients should be separated at least by a distance of 1.5 meters.
Unfortunately, it can also be experienced – added Karolina Böröcz – that in the less favorable economic situations hospitals are saved with disinfectants, there are few nurses and many patients and therefore there is a greater likelihood for infection.
According to Karolina Böröcz, where appropriate preventive measures are met, fewer infections of this type are recorded or the infection of the pathogen can be stopped.
Government Programme Against MRSA
The treatment of MRSA infection is an enormous expense for the National Insurance Fund, so it is fighted in all countries.
In England, for example, there is a government program to prevent and reduce cases of MRSA.
Apparently the program is successful, according to the data provided, MRSA infections show a declining trend in England.
The European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control (ECDC) has among its priorities the prevention of multi-resistant agents (among them MRSA) and the prevention of hospital infections due to these pathogens.
Negative alcohol control of police commander who caused a fatal accident
The official expert report on the case of the fatal accident caused by the commander of the police of the XXII district has been made.
It is possible to rule out the possibility that the resigned commander of the police of the XXII district, who on Tuesday struck and killed a passenger, was driving drunk or stunned, Attila Morvai, a spokesman for the Prosecutor General’s Office of the Capital, said on Friday after preparing the expert report on the case.
The expert report confirmed the outcome of the primary alcoholemia control that had already found that the former police commander did not consume alcoholic beverages before getting behind the wheel.
The then-chief of the police station of the XXII district, on Tuesday with his private vehicle in the Kossuth Lajos street of the XXII district struck a 55-year-old man, who intended to cross the street, but not in the area designated for pedestrians.
(This last fact, that is, that the pedestrian did not use the zebra to cross the street, according to the regulations of the Traffic Code are not mitigating circumstances, the driver must always give up the passage when bending.)
