Congress approves the transposition of the Mifid, which entered into force 1 November
Parallel to its parliamentary procedure, which ended today with the vote by the Congress of the amendments incorporated to the project in the Senate, the Government has submitted to public hearing the regulation that will develop the new law, with the aim of both entering into force before the end of the year.
The representatives of the different groups agreed to highlight the effort made by deputies and senators to negotiate and consensus the best regulations in order to guarantee the protection of investors and regulate in detail the activity of the entities so that the markets function efficiently.
The Mifid, which amends the Securities Market Law, means the modernization of financial markets, while strengthening investor protection, improving the supervisory powers of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and fostering cooperation between the different supervisors of the European Union.
The new regulation will allow financial advisory services to be provided to both specialized firms and natural or legal persons and creates a new type of financial services firms (ESIS), financial advisory companies (AFI), which join securities companies, securities agencies and portfolio companies.
In addition, it expands the number of systems for the execution of transactions on financial instruments, so that regulated secondary markets are added to multilateral trading systems and order internalization systems, which will compete with current stock exchange managers.
The Law also obliges investment services companies to disclose information on the market on the key aspects of their business profile, exposure to risk and forms of risk management and requires them to carry a record of all the transactions they carry out, to facilitate supervision by the CNMV.
In its passage by the Congressional Economy Commission, several modifications were incorporated, among which it is highlighted that debts titled are considered as a "complex" financial instrument given their high danger to the investor, which has been demonstrated with what happened with the debt of U.S. high-risk mortgages (subprime).
In addition, it took advantage of the transposition of the directive to legally delimit the functions that diplomats in Economics and Business can develop 30 years after the Royal Decree approved in 1977 that delimits the professional functions reserved for economists.
For its part, the Senate incorporated the creation of new figures in the financial sector, such as the mediator, who will work for another account, will not require the authorization of the CNMV and will be able to provide its services of product marketing and customer acquisition to different investment companies at the same time.
