Which insurance is suitable for me?
The car insurance, which covers the driver before possible accidents, represents an important expenditure that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, the age of the licence, the civil status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use of the car, among others.
Having a car is only the beginning.
And it is that, choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
First, we need to be clear about what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insured.
This commitment is materialized in an insurance contract, which stipulates that the company receives the value of the agreed premium in exchange for being responsible for the obligation to pay compensation in case of accident.
The premium is the price of the insurance, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, the age of the car, civil status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use that is given to it, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so that the more likely to suffer an accident, the higher the amount to pay.
It is for that reason that both the older 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics reflect that they have a lower rate of accidentality due to their prudence.
In addition, companies have come to the conclusion that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use given to the vehicle will influence the frequency, and thus the probability of having some type of crash.
As the frequency increases, the chances increase.
There are many variables that insurance companies have in mind when determining the premium price.
This is why the driver must study the situation well to choose that car insurance that best suits his profile.
We will expose here the most significant variables when choosing one or another type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insured, offers you a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 are faced with various disadvantages when it comes to contracting insurance at an affordable price, such as reduced driving experience and the age of the licence.
Although the ideal thing to be well insured is an all-risk insurance, there are other more economical options.
The most cautious drivers can opt for an all-risk franchise, so that they get the coverage of an all-risk insurance but at a more feasible price.
This type of agreement would require the customer to pay a part of the amount of the accident.
"The portion of the amount of the accident that the customer brings will be pre-established according to the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount," said Luis Noguera, the highest responsible in Spain of First Europe, online insurance mediator.
Another option is an extended third-party insurance, so that the customer is assured of protection against damages caused to third parties, although not against those caused in his own car.
In addition, it would be covered by theft, fire and the loss of the vehicle.
and a counsel.
If you are under the age of 25, try to be careful and avoid accidents as much as possible, as this will affect the bonus, which can reduce the cost of the insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction on the base rate owned by the company.
On the contrary, a penalty is a charge on that base fee.
The bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and the profit of the company.
If the company has had a good year, it will be able to increase the bonuses,” Noguera said.
After the age of 25, it is easier for drivers to contract insurance, since the accident rate is reduced thanks to accumulated experience.
For this reason, the most recommended is to contract a whole risk with franchise.
“Normally, young people cannot make use of the experience previously acquired when taking advantage of an accident, and even when driving,” says the director in Spain of the European company, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of driving, once the ‘fear of the newcomer’ has passed.
However, if the client is married but still has no children, it is preferable to negotiate insurance at all risk, as long as their economic situation allows it, of course.
For their part, marriages with children are considered by insurers as the public with the lowest rate of accidentality, so the charges will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be one to all risk with franchise (can be this of 300 euros), or, when you have a high level of bonification, one to third extended from the third year of life of the vehicle.
“They carry out a more relaxed driving and have greater purchasing power to afford the luxury of taking on a greater amount of franchise,” said Luis Noguera.
For retirees it is recommended to have an all-risk insurance with franchise (this being 150 euros), or one to third extended when you have a high level of bonification.
It must be said that car insurance is important, not only because it covers the driver in the event of possible accidents, but also because it represents an important expense, which is why it is essential to properly study the insurance that most suits us according to our personal situation.
